	<refnamediv>
		<refname>rrc_get_pulse_shape</refname>

		<refpurpose>Root Raised Cosine get pulse shape</refpurpose>
	</refnamediv>

	<refsynopsisdiv>
		<title>Calling Sequence</title>

		<synopsis> a = rrc_get_pulse_shape(b,c,d)</synopsis>
	</refsynopsisdiv>
	
	<refsection>

		<title>Parameters</title>

		<variablelist>                                                                            
			<varlistentry><term>a:</term>
				<listitem><para> Output pulse shape vector.</para></listitem></varlistentry>      
                         <varlistentry><term>b:</term>        
				<listitem><para> Roll off factor(non zero).</para></listitem></varlistentry>   
			<varlistentry><term>c:</term>        
				<listitem><para> integer filter length.</para></listitem></varlistentry>  
			<varlistentry><term>d:</term>        
				<listitem><para> integer upsampling factor.</para></listitem></varlistentry>        
		</variablelist>

	</refsection>



	<refsection>
		<title>Description</title>

		<para>Root Raised Cosine get pulse shape</para>
	
		<para>The function get_pulse_shape() gives the shape of the pulse which will be further used in upsampling and shaping of the input signal</para>

		<para> It is expected that the user inputs roll off factor, filter length and upsampling factor in scilab engine while calling the rrc_get_pulse_shape() function and expect the function to return pulse shape vector as output in scilab console.
		</para>
		
	</refsection>

	<refsection>
		<title>Examples</title>

		<programlisting role="example">b=0.5;&#10;c=6;&#10;d=8;&#10;a=rrc_get_pulse_shape(b,c,d)</programlisting>
	</refsection>

	<refsection>
		<title>Authors</title>

